firſt, theſe graces are neceſſarie to be in us, to enable us to all chriſtian duties, who of ourſelvs 
               2. Cor. 3. 5. 
               are not ſufficient (as of ourſelves) to doe ſo much as think any good, according to that of Chriſte 
                  Iohn. 15. 5. ſpeaking of himſelf, without me ye can doe nothing. And touching faith its ſaid of the Apoſtle, That without faith its impoſſible to pleaſe God Heb. 6.
            So that neither we ourſelvs, nor anie of our actions, can be acceptable to God, (even although they be the actions commaunded by God) unleſſe beleeving we doe them by 
